  <static seed="790" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/QuadraticEquations/solveQuad360.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve the equation.</p>
<p><m>{x\mathopen{}\left(x^{2}-25\right)} = 0</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="20" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left\{-5,5,0\right\}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Note that this is <em>not</em> a quadratic equation, as its degree is <m>3</m>. However, 
the factoring technique still applies</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {x\mathopen{}\left(x^{2}-25\right)} = 0 \amp \Rightarrow {x\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(x-5\right)}=0\\
                                \amp \Rightarrow x=-5\text{ or } x=5 \text{ or }x=0\\
        \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Each solution can be checked by substituting it into the original equation- this is left as an exercise.</p>
</solution>
